[+835] 24 Tigers Killed in Major Indian Tiger Reserve - None Left
item.description: One of India’s main tiger parks, Panna Tiger Reserve, has admitted that it has no tigers left. Just 3 years ago the park had at least 24 tigers, but park officials have been either unable or unwilling to protect the animals from poaching. Even more discouraging, Panna is now the second tiger reserve in India where numbers have dwindled to zero.
